definition.value: A deviation from the normal range of concentration of particles in urine.
An abnormally high urinary specific gravity, i.e., increased concentration of solutes in the urine.
Repeated occurrence of episodes of coughing, with each episode consisting of at least five minutes of continuous coughing.
Abnormally increased concentration of O-stearoylcarnitine in the blood circulation.
Abnormally increased concentration of palmitoylcarnitine in the blood circulation.

label.value: Decreased compound muscle action potential amplitude

definition.value: Increased level in the urine of a metabolite that results from collagen degradation, e.g., a fragment of a collagen produced by a collagenase or serine protease.

label.value: Abnormal circulating collagen degradation product concentration

definition.value: Abnormal concentration in the blood circulation of a metabolite that results from collagen degradation, e.g., a fragment of a collagen produced by a collagenase or serine protease.
Inflammatory cell infiltration surrounding precapillary pulmonary arteries (arterioles; 20-70 micrometer).

Restriction of arterial blood supply to a digit (finger or toe) associated with insufficient oxygenation to support the metabolic requirements of the digit. Clinical manifestations may include pain, pallor, lack of pulse, coldness, paresthesia, and paralysis.

label.value: Abnormal circulating organic amino compound concentration

definition.value: Any deviation from the normal concentration of an organic amino compound, defined as a compound formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by organyl groups.
An increased concentration of o-phosphoethanolamine in the blood circulation.
